  "prompt": "Which Harry Potter character was worst portrayed in the movies?",
  "response": "Opinions on which Harry Potter character was worst portrayed in the movies can vary widely among fans. Many argue that Ginny Weasley, played by Bonnie Wright, did not meet the expectations set by J.K. Rowling's books. In the novels, Ginny is depicted as a strong, independent, and charismatic character, while many fans feel that her portrayal in the movies didn't quite capture those qualities and seemed more subdued.\n\nAnother character that some fans feel was misrepresented is Albus Dumbledore, especially in the latter films. Michael Gambon's portrayal is often cited as different from the calm and composed Dumbledore of the books, with a more aggressive and sometimes erratic interpretation.\n\nThese views are subjective, and other fans might have different opinions. Ultimately, casting and character portrayal are complex processes influenced by numerous factors, including directorial interpretation, scriptwriting, and individual actor choices.",
